¿	Process Safety Information - Process safety information is maintained for the facility. The Process Safety Information Procedure (PAS-36) includes a description of how the Process Safety Information element is implemented; 

¿	Process Hazard Analysis - A detailed process hazard assessment, using a blended HAZOP and LOPA methodology, is conducted in the facility to ensure that it has been designed safely. The Process Hazard Analysis Procedure (PAS-04) includes a description of how the Process Hazard Analysis element is implemented; 

¿	Operating Procedures - A system is in place to ensure that updated and approved procedures cover all aspects of the facility's operation. The Operating Procedure Management System Practice Document (PA-01-GA-0112) includes a description of how the Operating Procedure element is to be implemented at Port Arthur; 

¿	Training - A training program has been established to ensure that personnel are well trained in the specific duties of their jobs. The Learning and Development Team is responsible for training of operations personnel; 

¿	Contractors - It is FHR's objective to partner with contractors that share the same safety philosophy. A dedicated, collective, and consistent approach by FHR and contractors will enhance and maintain the safety and health of our respective employees. The FHR-PA Contractor Safety Program element is included in the Contractor Safety Procedure (PAS-38); 

¿	Pre-startup Safety Review - A pre-startup safety review walk down and checklist is completed for each managed change that significantly impacts the Process Safety Information. The Maximo Management of Change Procedure (PAS-72) includes a description of how the Pre-startup Safety Review element is implemented; 

¿	Mechanical Integrity - An equipment inspection program is in place to ensure equipment remains in good condition to prevent releases. The Mechanical Integrity element i

s implemented and documented in FHR Standards and multiple Mechanical Integrity procedures, refer to the Organizational chart for more information; 

¿	Hot Work Permits - A work permit system is in place to ensure that work on process equipment and all hot work are conducted in a safe manner. The Hot Work Policy (PAS-15) includes a description of how the Hot Work Permits element is implemented;

¿	Management of Change - A management of change system has been established and implemented to ensure that any change is thoroughly reviewed prior to implementation. The Change Management Processes Procedure (PAS-35) includes a description of how the Management of Change element is implemented; 

¿	Incident Investigation - Incidents are investigated using one of several industry recognized methodologies, such as Cause Mapping, to determine system level root causes that can be remedied to prevent a recurrence. Employees and contractors involved in the incident are included on the investigation team. The Incident Investigation Procedure (PAS-8) includes a description of how the Incident Investigation element is implemented; 

¿	Emergency Planning and Response - An emergency action plan has been established, and the site is part of the Community Emergency Response Plan. The site's ICP One Plan includes a description of how the Emergency Planning and Response element is implemented; 

¿	Compliance Audits - Programs are audited annually; at least every three years through PSM compliance audits; and monthly safety inspections of the facility are conducted by cross functional teams. The Compliance Audit Procedure (PAS-67) includes a description of how the Compliance Audit element is implemented; 

¿	Trade Secrets - There are no Trade Secret issues at the facility. This is covered in the Trade Secrets Procedure (PAS-69)

